1
00:01:28,930 --> 00:01:35,030
[LIVE UP TO YOUR YOUTH]

2
00:01:35,430 --> 00:01:37,930
[Episode 3]

3
00:01:47,350 --> 00:01:48,680
What are you looking at?

4
00:02:03,710 --> 00:02:04,510
Do you like it?

5
00:02:07,290 --> 00:02:08,400
Thirty each.

6
00:02:08,740 --> 00:02:10,199
That's daylight robbery.

7
00:02:12,580 --> 00:02:14,530
You have to share a room with me.

8
00:02:14,650 --> 00:02:15,560
What bad luck.

9
00:02:15,890 --> 00:02:16,650
It's not like I insisted on

10
00:02:16,650 --> 00:02:17,910
moving into your room.

11
00:02:19,020 --> 00:02:20,740
Then just don't stay here.

12
00:02:21,250 --> 00:02:21,960
Anyway, now there's one extra person

13
00:02:21,960 --> 00:02:22,690
in this room.

14
00:02:22,860 --> 00:02:25,840
If I hadn't come, someone else
would've moved in anyway.

15
00:02:25,840 --> 00:02:26,710
I don't care.

16
00:02:27,300 --> 00:02:27,760
Anyway,

17
00:02:28,210 --> 00:02:30,010
you living here is annoying.

18
00:02:30,280 --> 00:02:32,110
You're being quite unreasonable.

19
00:02:32,110 --> 00:02:33,410
So what if I am?

20
00:02:34,210 --> 00:02:35,340
Have you had dinner?

21
00:02:36,100 --> 00:02:38,030
I have an audition. I'm not hungry.

22
00:02:39,740 --> 00:02:40,650
These clothes of mine

23
00:02:40,650 --> 00:02:42,710
are actually perfect for auditions.

24
00:02:42,950 --> 00:02:44,520
They're flashy and still decent.

25
00:02:44,520 --> 00:02:46,210
I have to charge more—50 a piece.

26
00:02:46,210 --> 00:02:47,740
You won't sell a single one.

27
00:02:47,970 --> 00:02:48,630
Don't worry.

28
00:02:48,630 --> 00:02:49,340
If there were an empty room,

29
00:02:49,340 --> 00:02:50,940
I would definitely move out.

30
00:02:52,540 --> 00:02:54,540
Don't make me wait forever for that.

31
00:03:13,730 --> 00:03:15,060
Mr. Zheng, long time no see.

32
00:03:15,060 --> 00:03:15,800
Yes, indeed.

33
00:03:15,960 --> 00:03:17,690
How are you and your wife doing?

34
00:03:17,840 --> 00:03:18,840
We're doing well.

35
00:03:19,360 --> 00:03:20,560
We're full of energy.

36
00:03:20,930 --> 00:03:21,730
How about you?

37
00:03:22,800 --> 00:03:23,610
Have you settled in?

38
00:03:23,610 --> 00:03:24,570
Where are you staying?

39
00:03:24,570 --> 00:03:25,970
I'm staying at a small hotel

40
00:03:25,970 --> 00:03:26,900
inside a hutong.

41
00:03:27,280 --> 00:03:27,710
OK.

42
00:03:28,650 --> 00:03:29,680
By the way, Mr. Zheng,

43
00:03:29,680 --> 00:03:30,730
this time I came,

44
00:03:30,840 --> 00:03:32,260
I plan to stay in Beijing.

45
00:03:32,470 --> 00:03:34,310
It's more convenient for my studies.

46
00:03:34,310 --> 00:03:35,900
Traveling back and forth before

47
00:03:35,900 --> 00:03:37,520
made it hard for me to learn properly.

48
00:03:37,520 --> 00:03:38,020
True.

49
00:03:38,630 --> 00:03:39,430
If you're planning to

50
00:03:39,430 --> 00:03:40,840
audition for orchestras

51
00:03:40,870 --> 00:03:42,530
or enter competitions later,

52
00:03:42,579 --> 00:03:43,579
you really do need

53
00:03:43,590 --> 00:03:45,320
more systematic improvement.

54
00:03:45,680 --> 00:03:47,610
Regular lessons are unavoidable.

55
00:03:47,740 --> 00:03:48,800
How about three classes a week?

56
00:03:48,800 --> 00:03:49,780
Of course, I'll give you a discount

57
00:03:49,780 --> 00:03:51,280
on tuition.

58
00:03:51,340 --> 00:03:52,600
Here, have some fruit!

59
00:03:54,090 --> 00:03:54,470
Come.

60
00:03:54,870 --> 00:03:55,280
Have some fruit.

61
00:03:55,280 --> 00:03:56,140
Zhuang Zhuang,

62
00:03:56,180 --> 00:03:57,110
have some fruit.

63
00:03:58,210 --> 00:03:59,140
Have some fruit.

64
00:03:59,340 --> 00:04:00,560
Thank you, Mrs. Zheng.

65
00:04:00,560 --> 00:04:01,190
When you're here,

66
00:04:01,190 --> 00:04:02,590
just make yourself at home.

67
00:04:02,590 --> 00:04:03,860
Please don't stand on ceremony.

68
00:04:03,860 --> 00:04:04,340
OK.

69
00:04:07,800 --> 00:04:08,930
That's really nice.

70
00:04:10,080 --> 00:04:11,740
You see, being young is great.

71
00:04:11,780 --> 00:04:13,310
She looks good in anything,

72
00:04:13,970 --> 00:04:14,970
right, Mr. Zheng?

73
00:04:16,040 --> 00:04:17,040
You look good too.

74
00:04:17,230 --> 00:04:18,630
You have your own beauty.

75
00:04:19,930 --> 00:04:21,190
You're never serious.

76
00:04:21,930 --> 00:04:23,600
How are your parents doing?

77
00:04:23,980 --> 00:04:25,110
They're doing well.

78
00:04:25,120 --> 00:04:26,680
They asked me to send you their regards.

79
00:04:26,680 --> 00:04:27,610
Really?

80
00:04:28,130 --> 00:04:29,660
Alright. When you go back home,

81
00:04:29,660 --> 00:04:31,100
say hello to them for me.

82
00:04:31,310 --> 00:04:31,680
OK.

83
00:04:31,820 --> 00:04:33,370
Alright, then I'll leave you to it.

84
00:04:33,370 --> 00:04:34,630
Mr. Zheng, time for class.

85
00:04:34,630 --> 00:04:35,310
Call me if you need anything.

86
00:04:35,310 --> 00:04:36,000
OK.

87
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:38,240
Then let's get started.

88
00:04:38,240 --> 00:04:38,510
OK.

89
00:04:46,810 --> 00:04:52,000
When I was young, my mother told me that

90
00:04:52,370 --> 00:04:57,500
the sea is my hometown.

91
00:04:57,930 --> 00:05:02,810
Born by the sea,

92
00:05:03,180 --> 00:05:08,240
raised by the sea.

93
00:05:08,740 --> 00:05:14,010
Oh, ocean, ocean,

94
00:05:14,040 --> 00:05:19,040
is where I grew up.

95
00:05:19,420 --> 00:05:24,510
Sea breeze blows, waves surge,

96
00:05:24,800 --> 00:05:30,010
drifting with me.

97
00:05:31,270 --> 00:05:32,040
Very good.

98
00:05:32,680 --> 00:05:34,180
This take is much better than before.

99
00:05:34,180 --> 00:05:35,980
You've improved a lot.

100
00:05:37,310 --> 00:05:40,110
Let's start from the beginning
and do it once more.

101
00:05:44,430 --> 00:05:45,290
Mr. Zheng, I...

102
00:05:46,960 --> 00:05:47,760
What's wrong?

103
00:05:50,390 --> 00:05:51,590
Just speak your mind.

104
00:05:52,180 --> 00:05:52,620
OK.

105
00:05:54,220 --> 00:05:55,270
I... I was wondering

106
00:05:55,270 --> 00:05:55,930
if I could pay my tuition

107
00:05:55,930 --> 00:05:57,720
at the end of the month.

108
00:05:57,930 --> 00:05:59,190
Because my money

109
00:05:59,190 --> 00:06:00,830
was stolen at the train station.

110
00:06:00,830 --> 00:06:01,870
I've been looking for a job recently,

111
00:06:01,870 --> 00:06:02,800
and they all said

112
00:06:03,160 --> 00:06:04,570
that I wouldn't get paid

113
00:06:04,630 --> 00:06:06,090
until the end of the month.

114
00:06:08,190 --> 00:06:08,920
I see.

115
00:06:13,190 --> 00:06:14,520
Did you tell your family

116
00:06:14,560 --> 00:06:15,720
about this?

117
00:06:17,630 --> 00:06:19,250
Then how are you
paying for your accommodation?

118
00:06:19,250 --> 00:06:20,450
I earned a bit myself,

119
00:06:20,510 --> 00:06:22,170
and a friend helped me out too.

120
00:06:26,660 --> 00:06:27,450
Understood.

121
00:06:32,110 --> 00:06:32,810
Don't worry

122
00:06:33,659 --> 00:06:34,590
about the money.

123
00:06:35,190 --> 00:06:36,990
Let's focus on the lesson first.

124
00:06:38,890 --> 00:06:40,090
Thank you, Mr. Zheng.

125
00:06:42,220 --> 00:06:43,390
Do you even know how to play?

126
00:06:43,390 --> 00:06:44,010
We two are playing chess here;

127
00:06:44,010 --> 00:06:45,070
stop running your mouth like a donkey.

128
00:06:45,070 --> 00:06:46,930
You're the donkey—
you don't even know

129
00:06:46,930 --> 00:06:47,590
how to play.

130
00:06:49,050 --> 00:06:50,960
Isn't this my famous little sister?

131
00:06:49,180 --> 00:06:51,610
[Bookstore]

132
00:06:51,770 --> 00:06:52,750
Where are you going?

133
00:06:52,750 --> 00:06:53,810
I have things to do.

134
00:06:56,000 --> 00:06:58,210
Hey… Did you guys drive

135
00:06:58,300 --> 00:07:00,360
the person in your room away already?

136
00:07:00,620 --> 00:07:01,750
There are too many people
in the courtyard.

137
00:07:01,750 --> 00:07:02,860
It's not convenient to talk.

138
00:07:02,860 --> 00:07:03,450
I was just about to

139
00:07:03,450 --> 00:07:04,870
report the situation to you.

140
00:07:04,870 --> 00:07:05,810
You can't rush this.

141
00:07:05,810 --> 00:07:07,000
It's like pulling nails.

142
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:08,160
You have to pull bit by bit.

143
00:07:08,160 --> 00:07:09,290
If you pull too fast,

144
00:07:09,600 --> 00:07:10,190
it snaps.

145
00:07:10,950 --> 00:07:12,410
So how far have you pulled?

146
00:07:12,510 --> 00:07:13,500
I just pulled it out,

147
00:07:13,500 --> 00:07:15,660
but it went back in.

148
00:07:16,130 --> 00:07:16,810
I've got something to do,
so I'll head off first.

149
00:07:16,810 --> 00:07:18,120
Wait, wait.

150
00:07:19,240 --> 00:07:20,370
Where are you going?

151
00:07:21,510 --> 00:07:22,570
That place up ahead

152
00:07:22,630 --> 00:07:23,680
sells door-knocker beef pancakes.

153
00:07:23,680 --> 00:07:25,500
You haven't eaten yet, have you?
I'll treat you.

154
00:07:25,500 --> 00:07:27,130
I... Thanks.

155
00:07:27,450 --> 00:07:28,680
But I can't eat anything lately.

156
00:07:28,680 --> 00:07:30,630
I have to lose weight for an audition.

157
00:07:30,630 --> 00:07:31,860
Stop trying to lose weight.

158
00:07:31,860 --> 00:07:33,810
You're already as thin as a rake.

159
00:07:33,980 --> 00:07:35,220
Excuse you?

160
00:07:35,330 --> 00:07:36,450
I'm not being rude.

161
00:07:36,680 --> 00:07:37,620
Look at those skinny arms

162
00:07:37,620 --> 00:07:38,750
and legs of yours—

163
00:07:39,120 --> 00:07:39,980
one strong wind

164
00:07:40,890 --> 00:07:42,220
and you'll snap in half.

165
00:07:43,060 --> 00:07:44,120
Are you mocking me?

166
00:07:44,360 --> 00:07:46,000
If I really snap in half out here

167
00:07:46,000 --> 00:07:47,000
and get stuck in the motel,

168
00:07:47,000 --> 00:07:47,860
will you take care of me?

169
00:07:47,860 --> 00:07:48,860
I'll take care of you.

170
00:07:48,860 --> 00:07:49,830
I have a bike.

171
00:07:49,860 --> 00:07:50,590
I'll sell it.

172
00:07:50,680 --> 00:07:52,330
And I can sell my saxophone too.

173
00:07:52,330 --> 00:07:54,060
I can even cover your rent for you.

174
00:07:54,060 --> 00:07:55,070
But then again,

175
00:07:55,680 --> 00:07:57,510
with your family background,

176
00:07:57,540 --> 00:08:00,130
you probably wouldn't let me pay anyway.

177
00:08:00,130 --> 00:08:01,160
I'm just trying to show

178
00:08:01,160 --> 00:08:01,960
my sincerity.

179
00:08:03,360 --> 00:08:03,890
Let's go.

180
00:08:06,630 --> 00:08:08,180
I've already made plans with someone.

181
00:08:08,180 --> 00:08:09,640
Let's do it some other day.

182
00:08:14,250 --> 00:08:15,420
Have a bite.

183
00:08:18,930 --> 00:08:20,600
Even if everything goes wrong,

184
00:08:20,600 --> 00:08:22,800
you should still take care of yourself.

185
00:08:22,930 --> 00:08:24,860
You have to look on the bright side.

186
00:08:25,110 --> 00:08:27,630
I failed the audition this time,

187
00:08:28,300 --> 00:08:29,700
not because of my acting,

188
00:08:30,160 --> 00:08:32,289
but because the director has no taste.

189
00:08:33,710 --> 00:08:35,100
You're blaming the director?

190
00:08:35,100 --> 00:08:36,559
You're getting bold, huh?

191
00:08:37,240 --> 00:08:38,169
You're really something.

192
00:08:38,169 --> 00:08:40,230
Seriously, who gave you the courage?

193
00:08:41,669 --> 00:08:42,100
Wait, look.

194
00:08:42,100 --> 00:08:43,700
Let's not talk about acting.

195
00:08:44,740 --> 00:08:45,220
Look.

196
00:08:45,240 --> 00:08:46,110
Take a look.

197
00:08:46,370 --> 00:08:47,720
What are you wearing?

198
00:08:50,120 --> 00:08:52,610
This outfit is perfectly fine.

199
00:08:53,290 --> 00:08:54,820
What are you talking about?

200
00:08:54,890 --> 00:08:56,320
I said my outfit

201
00:08:56,340 --> 00:08:57,400
is perfectly fine.

202
00:08:58,600 --> 00:09:00,400
It's about coordination, girl.

203
00:09:00,440 --> 00:09:02,030
Coordination matters, girl.

204
00:09:02,030 --> 00:09:03,740
Taste is also crucial for an actor.

205
00:09:03,740 --> 00:09:04,420
Girl,

206
00:09:04,670 --> 00:09:06,870
people judge you by what you wear first.

207
00:09:07,860 --> 00:09:08,460
I've told you so much,

208
00:09:08,460 --> 00:09:09,150
but you probably can't even take it in.

209
00:09:09,150 --> 00:09:09,770
Go back

210
00:09:09,770 --> 00:09:11,300
and think it over yourself.

211
00:09:40,410 --> 00:09:42,840
[We hope you enjoy your stay here.]

212
00:09:52,720 --> 00:09:53,220
Zhuang,

213
00:09:53,330 --> 00:09:54,390
have you eaten yet?

214
00:09:54,580 --> 00:09:55,480
Are you hungry?

215
00:09:55,700 --> 00:09:57,230
I bought a lot of food.

216
00:09:58,010 --> 00:09:59,280
This Beijing meat roll

217
00:09:59,410 --> 00:10:00,210
is delicious.

218
00:10:00,600 --> 00:10:01,600
Have you tried it?

219
00:10:01,790 --> 00:10:04,050
It's like a dough roll

220
00:10:04,260 --> 00:10:05,480
with meat filling inside.

221
00:10:05,480 --> 00:10:05,860
Here.

222
00:10:06,340 --> 00:10:06,790
Try it.

223
00:10:09,010 --> 00:10:09,970
It smells great.

224
00:10:10,080 --> 00:10:10,940
It's still hot.

225
00:10:20,810 --> 00:10:22,730
And there's traditional Beijing yogurt

226
00:10:22,730 --> 00:10:23,860
in a ceramic bottle.

227
00:10:28,530 --> 00:10:29,340
Try it.

228
00:10:30,480 --> 00:10:32,080
What's wrong with you today?

229
00:10:35,890 --> 00:10:36,490
Is it good?

230
00:10:38,630 --> 00:10:39,630
It's pretty good.

231
00:10:42,770 --> 00:10:43,240
Zhuang,

232
00:10:43,650 --> 00:10:45,180
you've got such good taste.

233
00:10:45,240 --> 00:10:46,630
No wonder the clothes you wear

234
00:10:46,630 --> 00:10:47,550
always look amazing,

235
00:10:47,550 --> 00:10:49,240
just like those in magazines.

236
00:10:49,860 --> 00:10:51,030
There are lots more magazines here.

237
00:10:51,030 --> 00:10:52,250
Read them if you like.

238
00:10:53,000 --> 00:10:53,370
OK.

239
00:11:01,480 --> 00:11:02,100
You know,

240
00:11:02,550 --> 00:11:03,740
dressing

241
00:11:04,290 --> 00:11:05,510
is kind of an art.

242
00:11:07,120 --> 00:11:08,820
The other day I went for an audition,

243
00:11:08,820 --> 00:11:10,000
and the assistant director told me

244
00:11:10,000 --> 00:11:11,780
to dress better next time.

245
00:11:12,410 --> 00:11:12,860
I

246
00:11:12,890 --> 00:11:14,610
walked around the streets

247
00:11:14,910 --> 00:11:16,000
trying to buy something nice,

248
00:11:16,000 --> 00:11:17,130
but I couldn't find anything
that looked good.

249
00:11:17,130 --> 00:11:18,840
I don't know how to
match clothes properly.

250
00:11:18,840 --> 00:11:20,580
I got so frustrated that I just ended up
buying a bunch of snacks instead.

251
00:11:20,580 --> 00:11:21,770
What role were you auditioning for?

252
00:11:21,770 --> 00:11:22,700
Tell me about it.

253
00:11:22,790 --> 00:11:24,130
I'll help you figure it out.

254
00:11:24,130 --> 00:11:26,390
It's kind of a vintage-style

255
00:11:26,500 --> 00:11:27,670
singing diva,

256
00:11:27,820 --> 00:11:29,890
and also that very bright,

257
00:11:29,910 --> 00:11:31,310
modern urban woman look,

258
00:11:31,340 --> 00:11:31,870
and

259
00:11:32,120 --> 00:11:33,650
-a office type...
-Hold on.

260
00:11:42,380 --> 00:11:43,040
I actually

261
00:11:43,320 --> 00:11:44,200
put together a few outfits

262
00:11:44,200 --> 00:11:45,390
the other day.

263
00:11:46,410 --> 00:11:47,010
Take a look

264
00:11:47,480 --> 00:11:49,140
and see if you like any of them.

265
00:11:51,060 --> 00:11:52,190
They all look great.

266
00:11:52,440 --> 00:11:53,100
Try them on.

267
00:11:53,340 --> 00:11:53,650
I...

268
00:11:54,940 --> 00:11:56,480
Is this really appropriate?

269
00:11:56,480 --> 00:11:57,440
Just try them.

270
00:11:57,530 --> 00:11:59,060
You've got such a great figure anyway—

271
00:11:59,060 --> 00:12:00,460
just think of it as helping me out
as a model.

272
00:12:00,460 --> 00:12:00,910
Sure.

273
00:12:01,780 --> 00:12:03,040
See which one you like.

274
00:12:04,650 --> 00:12:06,180
I think this one looks good.

275
00:12:15,170 --> 00:12:15,700
How is it?

276
00:12:17,600 --> 00:12:18,400
It looks good.

277
00:12:19,620 --> 00:12:21,580
You look so vibrant in bright colors.

278
00:12:21,580 --> 00:12:22,170
Really?

279
00:12:23,220 --> 00:12:23,550
Here.

280
00:12:30,240 --> 00:12:31,770
With this belt,

281
00:12:31,810 --> 00:12:33,340
it really looks different.

282
00:12:33,410 --> 00:12:35,870
If you like it, just take it
and wear it for a couple of days.

283
00:12:35,870 --> 00:12:37,270
Any others that you like?

284
00:12:38,780 --> 00:12:39,500
They all look good.

285
00:12:39,500 --> 00:12:40,630
And these jeans—

286
00:12:40,940 --> 00:12:43,030
the fit is amazing.

287
00:12:43,720 --> 00:12:46,050
I've never seen a cut
like this on the street.

288
00:12:46,050 --> 00:12:47,390
This would go well with this top—

289
00:12:47,390 --> 00:12:48,250
the purple one.

290
00:12:49,530 --> 00:12:49,870
OK.

291
00:12:57,360 --> 00:12:57,820
Zhuang,

292
00:12:58,340 --> 00:13:00,800
I find your accent
really familiar and kind.

293
00:13:02,080 --> 00:13:03,320
You're from Zhejiang too, right?

294
00:13:03,320 --> 00:13:04,520
Yes, I'm from Huzhou.

295
00:13:04,860 --> 00:13:05,860
I'm from Wenzhou.

296
00:13:06,150 --> 00:13:07,950
So we're from the same province.

297
00:13:11,550 --> 00:13:12,370
You should wear

298
00:13:12,370 --> 00:13:13,340
more bright colors—

299
00:13:13,340 --> 00:13:14,540
they really suit you.

300
00:13:14,770 --> 00:13:15,550
I think so.

301
00:13:17,080 --> 00:13:18,140
Thank you, Zhuang.

302
00:13:20,390 --> 00:13:21,320
You're welcome.

303
00:13:24,250 --> 00:13:28,500
Ah.

304
00:13:28,670 --> 00:13:29,630
Very good.

305
00:13:30,320 --> 00:13:34,720
Ah.

306
00:13:35,290 --> 00:13:36,310
Open your mouth.

307
00:13:37,100 --> 00:13:39,720
Ah.

308
00:13:39,770 --> 00:13:42,490
Open your mouth. Hold on.

309
00:13:42,530 --> 00:13:44,320
Good. Very good.

310
00:13:48,120 --> 00:13:48,960
Stop fighting.

311
00:13:48,960 --> 00:13:49,870
-What are you doing?
-Stop! Stop!

312
00:13:49,870 --> 00:13:50,480
Watch out.

313
00:13:50,720 --> 00:13:51,580
Stop fighting.

314
00:13:53,130 --> 00:13:53,630
Are you okay?

315
00:13:53,630 --> 00:13:54,060
Son.

316
00:13:54,670 --> 00:13:55,000
Son.

317
00:13:55,000 --> 00:13:56,130
Where did you get hurt?

318
00:13:56,130 --> 00:13:56,550
Son.

319
00:13:56,550 --> 00:13:56,840
Are you okay?

320
00:13:56,840 --> 00:13:57,290
Let go!

321
00:13:57,410 --> 00:13:59,010
What kind of teacher are you?

322
00:13:59,430 --> 00:14:00,890
-Son, does it hurt?
-He hit me first.

323
00:14:00,890 --> 00:14:01,580
Where did you get hit?

324
00:14:01,580 --> 00:14:02,940
Tell Mom, where does it hurt?

325
00:14:02,940 --> 00:14:03,670
My arm hurts.

326
00:14:03,860 --> 00:14:04,100
You...

327
00:14:04,100 --> 00:14:04,830
My arm hurts.

328
00:14:05,030 --> 00:14:06,120
How are you taking care of the kids?

329
00:14:06,120 --> 00:14:07,220
Why did you grab him like that?

330
00:14:07,220 --> 00:14:08,530
-I was trying to separate them.
-Stop explaining.

331
00:14:08,530 --> 00:14:09,530
I saw everything.

332
00:14:09,750 --> 00:14:11,100
Go get the principal here right now!

333
00:14:11,100 --> 00:14:12,290
What is going on?

334
00:14:12,370 --> 00:14:13,970
Can you even teach properly?

335
00:14:14,010 --> 00:14:15,410
How could you hit a child?

336
00:14:15,410 --> 00:14:16,760
I didn't.

337
00:14:16,870 --> 00:14:18,530
They were shoving each other.

338
00:14:18,740 --> 00:14:20,190
Did you grab him?

339
00:14:23,250 --> 00:14:23,970
Yes.

340
00:14:24,480 --> 00:14:25,170
I did grab them.

341
00:14:25,170 --> 00:14:25,720
But I was trying to

342
00:14:25,720 --> 00:14:26,650
separate them.

343
00:14:27,600 --> 00:14:28,340
The parents

344
00:14:28,390 --> 00:14:29,840
were watching right there.

345
00:14:29,840 --> 00:14:30,410
Anyway, under no circumstances

346
00:14:30,410 --> 00:14:31,390
should there be any physical contact

347
00:14:31,390 --> 00:14:32,450
with the children.

348
00:14:32,630 --> 00:14:33,870
Haven't you taught kids before?

349
00:14:33,870 --> 00:14:36,200
Don't you understand something so basic?

350
00:14:39,440 --> 00:14:40,500
All right, that's enough.

351
00:14:40,500 --> 00:14:41,330
I don't think

352
00:14:41,390 --> 00:14:42,860
you're suitable for this job.

353
00:14:42,860 --> 00:14:44,000
The parent is now

354
00:14:44,030 --> 00:14:45,670
refusing to let it go
and demanding a refund.

355
00:14:45,670 --> 00:14:46,750
You should just leave.

356
00:14:46,750 --> 00:14:47,770
It's not that I'm unsuitable for it.

357
00:14:47,770 --> 00:14:48,700
It's just that in that situation,

358
00:14:48,700 --> 00:14:49,220
I really had to...

359
00:14:49,220 --> 00:14:50,690
Stop explaining!

360
00:14:51,100 --> 00:14:52,930
The parents saw everything.

361
00:14:53,150 --> 00:14:54,220
You're still on probation—

362
00:14:54,220 --> 00:14:54,960
no pay.

363
00:14:56,410 --> 00:14:57,770
Please give me another chance,

364
00:14:57,770 --> 00:14:58,490
will you?

365
00:14:59,340 --> 00:15:00,680
I'll say it again.

366
00:15:00,980 --> 00:15:02,600
You're not suitable for this job.

367
00:15:02,600 --> 00:15:03,430
I promise that

368
00:15:03,530 --> 00:15:04,460
if the child acts up again,

369
00:15:04,460 --> 00:15:05,860
I'll handle it properly.

370
00:15:06,340 --> 00:15:07,050
If something like this happens again,

371
00:15:07,050 --> 00:15:08,270
I'll leave on my own.

372
00:15:08,910 --> 00:15:09,290
OK?

373
00:15:12,080 --> 00:15:13,210
But even if I agreed,

374
00:15:13,370 --> 00:15:14,120
how am I supposed to explain this

375
00:15:14,120 --> 00:15:14,980
to the parents?

376
00:15:15,410 --> 00:15:16,870
I'll go apologize to them.

377
00:15:17,240 --> 00:15:18,700
I'll go apologize to them.

378
00:15:22,140 --> 00:15:24,390
-Scissors, rock, paper…
-I'm really sorry about today.

379
00:15:24,390 --> 00:15:25,430
It was my fault.

380
00:15:25,540 --> 00:15:26,250
I hope you can

381
00:15:26,250 --> 00:15:27,680
give me another chance, will you?

382
00:15:27,680 --> 00:15:28,370
I promise it won't

383
00:15:28,370 --> 00:15:29,320
happen again.

384
00:15:29,320 --> 00:15:30,690
You don't need to apologize to us.

385
00:15:30,690 --> 00:15:31,560
It's useless.

386
00:15:31,700 --> 00:15:32,120
Yes.

387
00:15:32,140 --> 00:15:33,980
We're definitely going to change teachers.

388
00:15:33,980 --> 00:15:35,460
Luckily, the child
wasn't seriously injured.

389
00:15:35,460 --> 00:15:36,100
If anything had happened,

390
00:15:36,100 --> 00:15:37,010
your whole training center

391
00:15:37,010 --> 00:15:37,860
wouldn't have been able to
afford the compensation.

392
00:15:37,860 --> 00:15:38,440
Exactly.

393
00:15:39,120 --> 00:15:40,030
What bad luck.

394
00:15:41,120 --> 00:15:41,650
As a teacher,

395
00:15:41,650 --> 00:15:44,200
you need to be a bit
more patient in the future, alright?

396
00:15:44,200 --> 00:15:44,480
Come on.

397
00:15:44,480 --> 00:15:45,080
Auntie Li,

398
00:15:45,530 --> 00:15:46,830
how old is your child?

399
00:15:47,030 --> 00:15:47,630
Eight.

400
00:15:47,740 --> 00:15:48,410
Eight?

401
00:15:54,600 --> 00:15:55,860
Why are you here again?

402
00:15:56,200 --> 00:15:58,630
We don't know
when Director Weng will be back.

403
00:15:58,630 --> 00:16:00,290
Why don't you wait by the door?

404
00:16:18,000 --> 00:16:18,840
Are you still waiting there?

405
00:16:18,840 --> 00:16:19,360
Mr. Wu.

406
00:16:20,390 --> 00:16:21,650
Alright, I'm off work.

407
00:16:43,000 --> 00:16:43,660
Xu Shengli.

408
00:16:45,100 --> 00:16:45,760
Hello, sir.

409
00:16:46,420 --> 00:16:48,820
Don't come back
for the next couple of days.

410
00:16:48,980 --> 00:16:50,040
Director Weng is away on business.

411
00:16:50,040 --> 00:16:50,960
We don't know when

412
00:16:50,960 --> 00:16:51,760
he'll be back.

413
00:16:52,030 --> 00:16:53,090
On a business trip?

414
00:16:53,170 --> 00:16:54,200
Then... They...

415
00:16:54,960 --> 00:16:56,820
They didn't mean to mess with you.

416
00:16:57,010 --> 00:16:57,870
You know,

417
00:16:58,360 --> 00:16:59,910
there are many people

418
00:16:59,960 --> 00:17:01,170
coming to see Director Weng every day.

419
00:17:01,170 --> 00:17:03,370
Some just use it as an excuse

420
00:17:03,860 --> 00:17:05,060
to hand over scripts.

421
00:17:05,250 --> 00:17:06,609
It's led to a lot of jokes

422
00:17:06,660 --> 00:17:08,260
and ridiculous situations.

423
00:17:09,900 --> 00:17:10,579
Mr. Zou,

424
00:17:11,720 --> 00:17:13,450
Director Weng really knows me.

425
00:17:13,790 --> 00:17:14,790
We've worked together

426
00:17:14,790 --> 00:17:15,589
before.

427
00:17:17,000 --> 00:17:18,530
I even have a photo with him,

428
00:17:21,240 --> 00:17:22,609
and he's also said

429
00:17:23,000 --> 00:17:24,460
my writing is really good.

430
00:17:25,680 --> 00:17:26,280
Young man,

431
00:17:26,940 --> 00:17:29,540
it doesn't matter
whether I believe you or not.

432
00:17:29,900 --> 00:17:32,510
What matters is that
you need to understand something.

433
00:17:32,510 --> 00:17:33,500
Understand what exactly?

434
00:17:33,500 --> 00:17:34,570
I understand that

435
00:17:35,640 --> 00:17:36,820
you love writing

436
00:17:37,140 --> 00:17:38,810
and want to be an artistic young man—

437
00:17:38,810 --> 00:17:39,700
there's nothing wrong with that.

438
00:17:39,700 --> 00:17:40,940
As a hobby writer,

439
00:17:41,270 --> 00:17:43,090
I think your work

440
00:17:43,850 --> 00:17:45,400
is quite good.

441
00:17:47,310 --> 00:17:49,400
But if you want to make a living

442
00:17:49,610 --> 00:17:50,610
from writing,

443
00:17:51,350 --> 00:17:53,550
that's a completely different matter.

444
00:17:54,330 --> 00:17:55,330
Someone like you,

445
00:17:55,830 --> 00:17:57,420
turning a hobby into competition

446
00:17:57,420 --> 00:17:59,220
for other people's livelihood,

447
00:17:59,660 --> 00:18:01,190
is only setting yourself up

448
00:18:01,510 --> 00:18:03,440
for trouble.

449
00:18:03,880 --> 00:18:04,920
Take my advice.

450
00:18:05,310 --> 00:18:07,340
Keep writing

451
00:18:07,770 --> 00:18:08,860
as a hobby;

452
00:18:09,500 --> 00:18:10,110
that way,

453
00:18:11,030 --> 00:18:13,290
you might actually find real happiness.

454
00:18:14,750 --> 00:18:15,480
I'm leaving.

455
00:18:17,960 --> 00:18:18,460
Mr. Zou,

456
00:18:20,590 --> 00:18:21,570
please wait.

457
00:18:33,850 --> 00:18:34,510
Mr. Zou,

458
00:18:35,350 --> 00:18:36,480
here is my address

459
00:18:35,460 --> 00:18:37,650
[Seasons Change Hotel
—Xu Shengli]

460
00:18:36,480 --> 00:18:37,720
and phone number in Beijing.

461
00:18:37,720 --> 00:18:39,160
If Director Weng returns,

462
00:18:39,160 --> 00:18:39,590
or

463
00:18:40,200 --> 00:18:42,730
if you have any suggestions
about the script,

464
00:18:42,810 --> 00:18:44,300
please feel free to contact me anytime.

465
00:18:44,300 --> 00:18:47,460
[Seasons Change Hotel
—Xu Shengli]

466
00:18:55,310 --> 00:18:56,040
I'm leaving.

467
00:19:06,500 --> 00:19:06,910
Xu.

468
00:19:10,180 --> 00:19:11,040
Zhuang Zhuang.

469
00:19:11,810 --> 00:19:13,330
Why do you look so down?

470
00:19:14,160 --> 00:19:15,110
No.

471
00:19:15,530 --> 00:19:15,900
No.

472
00:19:16,610 --> 00:19:17,930
I've been out all day.

473
00:19:18,140 --> 00:19:19,200
I'm a little tired.

474
00:19:22,420 --> 00:19:24,110
You've just arrived in Beijing.

475
00:19:24,110 --> 00:19:25,280
You should cheer up.

476
00:19:26,810 --> 00:19:29,180
Be positive and full of hope.

477
00:19:30,880 --> 00:19:31,350
Yes.

478
00:19:31,980 --> 00:19:33,200
Be positive

479
00:19:33,850 --> 00:19:36,200
and full of hope!

480
00:19:37,700 --> 00:19:38,960
What are you doing? Xu!

481
00:19:39,200 --> 00:19:40,070
What are you doing?

482
00:19:40,070 --> 00:19:40,750
Don't shout.

483
00:19:40,750 --> 00:19:41,150
You...

484
00:19:42,090 --> 00:19:42,550
Shut up!

485
00:19:42,790 --> 00:19:43,480
Help!

486
00:19:43,500 --> 00:19:44,250
Don't shout!

487
00:19:45,110 --> 00:19:46,040
What's going on?

488
00:19:46,160 --> 00:19:47,070
They're fighting?

489
00:19:47,070 --> 00:19:47,440
They're fighting?

490
00:19:47,440 --> 00:19:48,500
They're fighting.

491
00:19:50,440 --> 00:19:51,500
Help!

492
00:19:51,660 --> 00:19:52,390
Don't shout.

493
00:19:54,480 --> 00:19:55,630
What a deep grudge.

494
00:19:55,920 --> 00:19:56,770
Who? Who is it?

495
00:19:56,980 --> 00:19:57,510
Who is it?

496
00:19:57,830 --> 00:19:58,790
Xu.

497
00:19:59,010 --> 00:20:00,000
Which Xu guy?

498
00:20:00,750 --> 00:20:01,860
Xu Shengli.

499
00:20:06,580 --> 00:20:07,640
Are we going in or not?

500
00:20:07,640 --> 00:20:08,320
We go in!

501
00:20:08,760 --> 00:20:09,960
Little Northeasterner!

502
00:20:09,960 --> 00:20:10,550
Don't shout.

503
00:20:10,550 --> 00:20:11,250
Bro.

504
00:20:14,140 --> 00:20:14,720
Help!

505
00:20:14,810 --> 00:20:15,880
Hitting women isn't right.

506
00:20:15,880 --> 00:20:16,830
Go! Grab your gear.

507
00:20:16,830 --> 00:20:17,360
Let's go.

508
00:20:18,790 --> 00:20:19,320
Bro.

509
00:20:19,460 --> 00:20:20,310
Bro, over here.

510
00:20:20,310 --> 00:20:21,000
Let go!

511
00:20:21,570 --> 00:20:23,650
Little Northeasterner!

512
00:20:26,120 --> 00:20:27,120
The money is here.

513
00:20:27,780 --> 00:20:28,370
Go away!

514
00:20:28,850 --> 00:20:30,960
Go away! Get away!

515
00:20:31,010 --> 00:20:31,590
Go away!

516
00:20:32,640 --> 00:20:33,300
Who is that?

517
00:20:33,880 --> 00:20:34,680
What are you doing?

518
00:20:34,680 --> 00:20:35,550
-Stop!
-Stop!

519
00:20:35,640 --> 00:20:36,250
Stand right there!

520
00:20:36,250 --> 00:20:37,050
Go, go, go! Hurry!

521
00:20:37,050 --> 00:20:37,650
Don't run!

522
00:20:37,680 --> 00:20:38,610
Don't run!

523
00:20:39,400 --> 00:20:40,000
Don't run!

524
00:20:40,850 --> 00:20:42,700
Charge!

525
00:20:42,920 --> 00:20:43,350
Stop!

526
00:20:43,380 --> 00:20:43,740
Don't run!

527
00:20:43,740 --> 00:20:44,880
Charge!

528
00:20:44,980 --> 00:20:45,910
Xu! Xu!

529
00:20:46,270 --> 00:20:46,850
Xu!

530
00:20:48,530 --> 00:20:49,570
My money!

531
00:20:52,640 --> 00:20:53,270
Xu!

532
00:20:54,670 --> 00:20:55,620
Somebody help!

533
00:20:56,900 --> 00:20:57,400
Xu!

534
00:21:01,820 --> 00:21:03,720
Thanks for saving me just now.

535
00:21:04,050 --> 00:21:04,710
No problem.

536
00:21:05,500 --> 00:21:06,660
We weren't even trying to save you;

537
00:21:06,660 --> 00:21:08,330
we were just saving the beauty.

538
00:21:08,330 --> 00:21:09,120
Tang,

539
00:21:09,310 --> 00:21:11,310
-I've seen robbers on the street,
-The police are here.

540
00:21:11,310 --> 00:21:12,290
but I've never seen anyone

541
00:21:12,290 --> 00:21:13,090
beat someone this badly.

542
00:21:13,090 --> 00:21:13,680
So I think

543
00:21:13,680 --> 00:21:14,770
this might be a revenge case.

544
00:21:14,770 --> 00:21:15,660
The person who got beaten

545
00:21:15,660 --> 00:21:16,570
looks pretty honest.

546
00:21:16,570 --> 00:21:18,050
He doesn't seem like someone
who would cause this kind of trouble.

547
00:21:18,050 --> 00:21:19,010
So, I think...

548
00:21:19,010 --> 00:21:20,250
What do you mean by "you think?"

549
00:21:20,250 --> 00:21:21,330
You've gotten quite capable lately,

550
00:21:21,330 --> 00:21:21,880
haven't you?

551
00:21:21,880 --> 00:21:23,140
You're solving cases now?

552
00:21:23,140 --> 00:21:24,200
I wouldn't dare to.

553
00:21:24,590 --> 00:21:25,250
That's him.

554
00:21:26,110 --> 00:21:26,750
Officer Tang.

555
00:21:26,750 --> 00:21:27,200
You're here.

556
00:21:27,200 --> 00:21:28,740
Are you lining up to welcome me?

557
00:21:28,740 --> 00:21:29,110
Yes.

558
00:21:30,140 --> 00:21:31,090
You must be Xu Shengli?

559
00:21:31,090 --> 00:21:31,400
Yes.

560
00:21:31,460 --> 00:21:32,460
Here, have a seat.

561
00:21:34,720 --> 00:21:35,660
Is your head okay?

562
00:21:35,660 --> 00:21:37,380
I'm fine, I just got it bandaged.

563
00:21:37,380 --> 00:21:38,010
Could you cooperate with us

564
00:21:38,010 --> 00:21:38,790
and tell us what happened?

565
00:21:38,790 --> 00:21:40,450
No problem. No problem at all.

566
00:21:41,790 --> 00:21:43,240
Did you see clearly who hit you?

567
00:21:43,240 --> 00:21:44,170
Do you know them?

568
00:21:44,790 --> 00:21:46,060
He came up from behind

569
00:21:46,140 --> 00:21:47,110
and hit me with a stick.

570
00:21:47,110 --> 00:21:48,090
My vision went black,

571
00:21:48,090 --> 00:21:49,550
I... I didn't see clearly.

572
00:21:49,640 --> 00:21:51,010
How many of them were there?

573
00:21:51,010 --> 00:21:52,890
About three or four.

574
00:21:53,030 --> 00:21:53,380
Yeah.

575
00:21:54,240 --> 00:21:55,770
How much did they take from you?

576
00:21:55,770 --> 00:21:57,040
They took 1,500 yuan.

577
00:21:57,740 --> 00:21:58,900
Were you guys at the scene too?

578
00:21:58,900 --> 00:21:59,250
No,

579
00:21:59,270 --> 00:22:01,400
They were gone by the time we got there.

580
00:22:01,420 --> 00:22:03,020
I was there. I saw it.

581
00:22:04,250 --> 00:22:05,250
You live here too?

582
00:22:06,160 --> 00:22:06,970
Officer,

583
00:22:07,180 --> 00:22:08,580
I think this was revenge.

584
00:22:10,310 --> 00:22:10,940
Revenge?

585
00:22:12,330 --> 00:22:13,610
Two of them looked exactly like

586
00:22:13,610 --> 00:22:14,920
the people who stole my wallet

587
00:22:14,920 --> 00:22:16,460
a couple of days ago at the train station.

588
00:22:16,460 --> 00:22:16,880
Xu,

589
00:22:16,900 --> 00:22:18,180
you even helped me chase them then.

590
00:22:18,180 --> 00:22:20,040
Maybe they were holding a grudge.

591
00:22:20,160 --> 00:22:20,420
Yes.

592
00:22:21,570 --> 00:22:23,140
That's quite something, young lady.

593
00:22:23,140 --> 00:22:24,800
That's a very important lead.

594
00:22:25,220 --> 00:22:26,150
Write that down.

595
00:22:29,850 --> 00:22:30,380
Alright.

596
00:22:30,810 --> 00:22:31,550
Alright, we've noted down

597
00:22:31,550 --> 00:22:32,550
your statements.

598
00:22:32,640 --> 00:22:34,660
We'll notify you if there's any news.

599
00:22:34,660 --> 00:22:36,250
Are these two long-term residents here?

600
00:22:36,250 --> 00:22:36,920
They just moved in.

601
00:22:36,920 --> 00:22:38,720
They just paid one month's rent.

602
00:22:38,750 --> 00:22:40,680
Everyone who comes here is a guest.

603
00:22:40,700 --> 00:22:41,920
Don't just take their money.

604
00:22:41,920 --> 00:22:44,250
Make sure you also
take care of them properly.

605
00:22:44,250 --> 00:22:46,110
You all should be more attentive.

606
00:22:46,960 --> 00:22:47,680
Get some rest.

607
00:22:47,680 --> 00:22:48,680
Wait for our news.

608
00:22:49,300 --> 00:22:49,630
Sure.

609
00:22:49,740 --> 00:22:50,810
Everyone, take it easy.

610
00:22:50,810 --> 00:22:51,900
Thank you, Officer.

611
00:22:51,900 --> 00:22:52,400
Thank you.

612
00:22:52,400 --> 00:22:53,000
Thank you.

613
00:22:53,010 --> 00:22:53,480
Goodbye.

614
00:22:53,480 --> 00:22:54,810
I'll walk you out, Tang.

615
00:22:55,460 --> 00:22:56,030
Xu!

616
00:22:56,140 --> 00:22:56,540
Hurry.

617
00:22:57,790 --> 00:22:58,420
What's going on?

618
00:22:58,420 --> 00:22:59,080
Xu Shengli.

619
00:22:59,420 --> 00:23:03,100
[Guest Room]

620
00:23:03,170 --> 00:23:06,650
[Seasons Change Hotel]

621
00:23:06,700 --> 00:23:07,830
Why isn't he snoring

622
00:23:07,850 --> 00:23:08,930
or grind his teeth?

623
00:23:09,050 --> 00:23:09,900
He's been asleep for a day and a night.

624
00:23:09,900 --> 00:23:10,890
He's practically glued to the bed.

625
00:23:10,890 --> 00:23:12,460
He really thinks he's a big shot.

626
00:23:12,460 --> 00:23:12,810
With a hit like that

627
00:23:12,810 --> 00:23:13,660
to his head,

628
00:23:13,660 --> 00:23:14,720
could it affect his brain?

629
00:23:14,720 --> 00:23:16,700
-It's fine. It's fine.
-From now on...

630
00:23:16,700 --> 00:23:17,720
Who hasn't been beaten up before?

631
00:23:17,720 --> 00:23:18,350
Wake up.

632
00:23:18,380 --> 00:23:19,600
But I keep saying...

633
00:23:20,740 --> 00:23:21,500
Move aside.

634
00:23:22,310 --> 00:23:23,840
Can you stop bothering him?

635
00:23:25,740 --> 00:23:27,400
Let me make it thicker for you.

636
00:23:41,830 --> 00:23:42,420
Xu,

637
00:23:43,140 --> 00:23:44,270
take your medicine.

638
00:23:50,720 --> 00:23:51,780
I don't want to eat.

639
00:23:55,160 --> 00:23:56,620
Then do you want some food?

640
00:23:58,460 --> 00:23:59,370
No.

641
00:23:59,720 --> 00:24:00,460
Or else,

642
00:24:00,510 --> 00:24:02,330
tell her what you want.

643
00:24:03,720 --> 00:24:04,250
Miss,

644
00:24:04,810 --> 00:24:07,070
maybe we should take him to the hospital.

645
00:24:07,350 --> 00:24:09,010
Don't let that writer's brain

646
00:24:09,140 --> 00:24:11,140
get damaged from getting beaten up.

647
00:24:11,200 --> 00:24:12,250
Why go to a hospital?

648
00:24:12,250 --> 00:24:13,370
It's not as comfortable as here.

649
00:24:13,370 --> 00:24:14,330
Right? He's been taken care of
in the room.

650
00:24:14,330 --> 00:24:15,330
This is better than…

651
00:24:15,330 --> 00:24:16,790
Taking him away works too.

652
00:24:18,010 --> 00:24:20,070
Do you guys have nothing better to do?

653
00:24:20,660 --> 00:24:21,420
Don't you have anything upsetting going on

654
00:24:21,420 --> 00:24:22,610
in your own lives?

655
00:24:22,960 --> 00:24:23,460
Miss,

656
00:24:24,350 --> 00:24:26,000
just being alive is already

657
00:24:26,000 --> 00:24:26,730
a hard thing.

658
00:24:26,770 --> 00:24:27,880
Raphael, Michelangelo,

659
00:24:27,880 --> 00:24:28,850
Leonardo da Vinci—

660
00:24:28,850 --> 00:24:29,550
nowadays we see them

661
00:24:29,550 --> 00:24:30,830
as great artists,

662
00:24:30,850 --> 00:24:31,250
right?

663
00:24:31,610 --> 00:24:32,270
But back then,

664
00:24:32,270 --> 00:24:35,330
they were basically just
working for the aristocrats.

665
00:24:35,400 --> 00:24:37,030
If you want to heal your soul,
you've got to listen to some music.

666
00:24:37,030 --> 00:24:37,970
Ignore them.

667
00:24:38,070 --> 00:24:39,500
I'll go get you something to eat.

668
00:24:39,500 --> 00:24:41,000
You know, Plato—

669
00:24:41,070 --> 00:24:41,570
well, maybe it was

670
00:24:41,570 --> 00:24:42,510
Aristotle—once said that

671
00:24:42,510 --> 00:24:44,940
suffering is the best soil

672
00:24:45,070 --> 00:24:46,310
for nourishing art.

673
00:24:46,510 --> 00:24:47,920
Here, let me show you

674
00:24:47,960 --> 00:24:49,640
what Bach's sense of humor is like.

675
00:24:49,640 --> 00:24:52,090
There is actually a misconception here.

676
00:24:52,110 --> 00:24:54,290
Seriousness isn't all there

677
00:24:54,380 --> 00:24:55,440
is to Bach's music.

678
00:24:55,480 --> 00:24:56,540
Don't just read it.

679
00:25:55,820 --> 00:26:00,150
[Notes in motion,
chasing dreams without ever stopping.]

680
00:26:02,310 --> 00:26:03,250
Have you eaten, Little Northeasterner?

681
00:26:03,250 --> 00:26:03,890
Are you heading out?

682
00:26:03,790 --> 00:26:12,300
[A home away from home, only better.]

683
00:26:03,960 --> 00:26:05,220
I have something to do.

684
00:26:12,350 --> 00:26:20,960
[Guest Room]

685
00:26:14,180 --> 00:26:15,510
Come on, Zhuang Zhuang.

686
00:26:15,980 --> 00:26:16,640
Ms. Zhuang,

687
00:26:17,000 --> 00:26:19,070
are you heading off
to teach the kids again?

688
00:26:19,070 --> 00:26:19,720
No.

689
00:26:20,090 --> 00:26:20,850
I got fired.

690
00:26:21,720 --> 00:26:23,720
You got fired and you're this happy?

691
00:26:23,790 --> 00:26:25,090
So you found a new job?

692
00:26:25,250 --> 00:26:25,930
Not yet.

693
00:26:26,200 --> 00:26:27,010
I'm just about to head out

694
00:26:27,010 --> 00:26:27,930
and look for it.

695
00:26:28,000 --> 00:26:29,200
Maybe I'll get lucky.

696
00:26:29,250 --> 00:26:29,810
Go ahead.

697
00:26:29,310 --> 00:26:34,060
[Guest Room]

698
00:26:30,480 --> 00:26:32,410
I should learn from your attitude.

699
00:26:32,790 --> 00:26:33,570
By the way,

700
00:26:34,550 --> 00:26:35,420
tell Xu

701
00:26:35,420 --> 00:26:36,740
that he hasn't fully recovered yet,

702
00:26:36,740 --> 00:26:39,000
so he shouldn't go out unless necessary.

703
00:26:39,660 --> 00:26:40,320
Ms. Zhuang,

704
00:26:40,790 --> 00:26:41,990
you're a good person.

705
00:26:42,080 --> 00:26:43,460
He's a good person too.

706
00:26:44,190 --> 00:26:46,120
But let me say a couple more things:

707
00:26:46,530 --> 00:26:47,440
sometimes

708
00:26:47,530 --> 00:26:48,790
you can't take a man's vulnerability

709
00:26:48,790 --> 00:26:49,650
too seriously.

710
00:26:50,330 --> 00:26:51,530
Right now his head is full of

711
00:26:51,530 --> 00:26:53,000
sentimental things.

712
00:26:53,440 --> 00:26:56,040
Once he gets better,
he'll forget all about it.

713
00:26:56,530 --> 00:26:57,660
That would be great.

714
00:26:58,510 --> 00:27:00,440
Isn't it good for him to get better?

715
00:27:02,250 --> 00:27:03,580
Remember to remind him.

716
00:27:06,530 --> 00:27:07,140
OK.

717
00:27:20,290 --> 00:27:20,890
Very good.

718
00:27:21,550 --> 00:27:22,550
The class today

719
00:27:23,160 --> 00:27:24,140
was of high quality.

720
00:27:24,140 --> 00:27:25,680
It shows you kept my pointers

721
00:27:25,680 --> 00:27:26,550
in mind

722
00:27:26,640 --> 00:27:27,510
while singing.

723
00:27:27,880 --> 00:27:28,680
That's great.

724
00:27:29,440 --> 00:27:31,830
Okay, let's continue. Come on.

725
00:27:35,770 --> 00:27:36,370
Mr. Zheng,

726
00:27:36,590 --> 00:27:37,520
I wanted to ask,

727
00:27:37,660 --> 00:27:38,990
if you know of any need

728
00:27:39,220 --> 00:27:40,240
for recording backing vocals

729
00:27:40,240 --> 00:27:41,970
or vocal teaching assistants.

730
00:27:47,750 --> 00:27:48,640
I see.

731
00:27:49,610 --> 00:27:50,470
Zhuang Zhuang,

732
00:27:51,840 --> 00:27:54,500
you're thinking that
since you're already out here,

733
00:27:54,500 --> 00:27:55,500
you should do more

734
00:27:56,100 --> 00:27:56,790
to help your family

735
00:27:56,790 --> 00:27:58,060
lighten the burden.

736
00:27:58,770 --> 00:27:59,570
I understand.

737
00:28:00,310 --> 00:28:01,400
But you must know,

738
00:28:01,790 --> 00:28:02,420
you are different from

739
00:28:02,420 --> 00:28:04,080
the kids at the conservatory.

740
00:28:04,550 --> 00:28:05,880
Now is the most critical moment

741
00:28:05,880 --> 00:28:07,240
for your competition prep

742
00:28:07,240 --> 00:28:08,810
and troupe audition.

743
00:28:10,810 --> 00:28:11,700
You must pay special attention

744
00:28:11,700 --> 00:28:13,160
to protecting your voice.

745
00:28:13,180 --> 00:28:14,140
Our daily practice

746
00:28:14,140 --> 00:28:15,380
is already very draining.

747
00:28:15,380 --> 00:28:17,140
If you go out to sing

748
00:28:17,200 --> 00:28:17,960
or work,

749
00:28:20,220 --> 00:28:21,420
I'll be very worried.

750
00:28:22,940 --> 00:28:23,740
I understand.

751
00:28:28,240 --> 00:28:29,100
Zhuang Zhuang,

752
00:28:30,380 --> 00:28:31,270
don't worry

753
00:28:32,380 --> 00:28:33,440
about the tuition.

754
00:28:34,440 --> 00:28:36,370
Just focus on your lessons for now.

755
00:28:37,130 --> 00:28:38,330
Thank you, Mr. Zheng.

756
00:28:40,420 --> 00:28:42,050
-Sign it.
-Little Northeasterner.

757
00:28:42,050 --> 00:28:43,570
Where is my letter?

758
00:28:43,570 --> 00:28:44,440
You're in high spirits.

759
00:28:44,440 --> 00:28:45,480
Is your head better?

760
00:28:45,480 --> 00:28:46,810
I'm sharp.

761
00:28:46,900 --> 00:28:47,510
Look.

762
00:28:50,070 --> 00:28:50,830
Your moneymaker.

763
00:28:50,830 --> 00:28:52,030
You gotta protect it.

764
00:28:53,290 --> 00:28:54,140
This is a registered letter.

765
00:28:54,140 --> 00:28:55,220
I had to keep it separate for you.

766
00:28:55,220 --> 00:28:56,270
Thank you.

767
00:28:57,610 --> 00:28:58,790
Sign first.

768
00:29:01,210 --> 00:29:04,730
[Rejection Notice
from the Capital Film Studio]

769
00:29:19,810 --> 00:29:20,340
Alright.

770
00:29:20,980 --> 00:29:23,710
He started strong,
ended up going downhill, huh?

771
00:29:24,180 --> 00:29:25,550
[Author: Xu Shengli] [Rejection]

772
00:29:30,830 --> 00:29:33,220
[The author of "As High as the Sky",
Xu Shengli] [Rejection]

773
00:29:35,260 --> 00:29:36,570
[The author of "As High as the Sky",
Xu Shengli] [Rejection]

774
00:29:48,070 --> 00:29:50,480
["As High as the Sky"]

775
00:29:53,770 --> 00:29:56,310
["As High as the Sky"]

776
00:30:05,230 --> 00:30:07,510
[The author of "As High as the Sky",
Xu Shengli] [Sixth Draft]

777
00:30:10,050 --> 00:30:10,740
How much is it?

778
00:30:10,740 --> 00:30:11,380
100 yuan.

779
00:30:11,570 --> 00:30:12,440
100 yuan?

780
00:30:12,480 --> 00:30:13,530
-It's too expensive.
-It's too expensive.

781
00:30:13,530 --> 00:30:14,750
You think that's expensive?

782
00:30:14,750 --> 00:30:15,940
You have good taste.

783
00:30:16,460 --> 00:30:17,460
This is made for export.

784
00:30:17,460 --> 00:30:18,720
Genuine export goods.

785
00:30:19,010 --> 00:30:19,440
[Music Conservatory Student Union]

786
00:30:19,460 --> 00:30:19,890
[Summer Work-Study
Program Registration Desk]

787
00:30:19,570 --> 00:30:20,090
This is our

788
00:30:20,090 --> 00:30:21,350
work-study program.

789
00:30:21,380 --> 00:30:22,330
Feel free to take a look.

790
00:30:21,440 --> 00:30:21,690
[Music Conservatory Student Union]

791
00:30:21,710 --> 00:30:21,910
[Summer Work-Study
Program Registration Desk]

792
00:30:22,210 --> 00:30:24,510
[CHUN LAI JIE]

793
00:30:22,590 --> 00:30:23,350
Right. If there's anything you don't know,

794
00:30:23,350 --> 00:30:24,420
you can ask me.

795
00:30:25,000 --> 00:30:25,900
Here is our

796
00:30:25,900 --> 00:30:26,750
training content.

797
00:30:26,750 --> 00:30:27,740
It includes product introduction,

798
00:30:27,740 --> 00:30:28,530
sales techniques,

799
00:30:28,530 --> 00:30:29,310
stall management,

800
00:30:29,310 --> 00:30:30,480
and things to note.

801
00:30:30,510 --> 00:30:31,440
The contact number is at the bottom.

802
00:30:31,170 --> 00:30:34,070
[CHUN LAI JIE]

803
00:30:31,510 --> 00:30:32,180
OK.

804
00:30:32,640 --> 00:30:33,070
Excuse me,

805
00:30:33,070 --> 00:30:34,570
would you like to learn about
the work-study program?

806
00:30:34,570 --> 00:30:35,170
Thank you.

807
00:30:36,250 --> 00:30:37,030
This is a program

808
00:30:37,030 --> 00:30:38,660
jointly organized by the school
and the local community,

809
00:30:38,660 --> 00:30:39,160
designed to

810
00:30:39,160 --> 00:30:40,220
make use of students' free time

811
00:30:40,220 --> 00:30:41,000
for work-study.

812
00:30:40,250 --> 00:30:40,600
[Music Conservatory Student Union]

813
00:30:40,620 --> 00:30:41,020
[Rules for the Summer Work-Study Program]

814
00:30:41,080 --> 00:30:41,980
[Organization and Purpose of the Program]
[Supply and Sales Arrangement]

815
00:30:42,000 --> 00:30:43,540
[Registration Requirements and Enrollment]
[Training Schedule]

816
00:30:44,480 --> 00:30:45,460
How do I sign up?

817
00:30:45,460 --> 00:30:46,440
Here is the application form.

818
00:30:46,440 --> 00:30:47,500
You can take a look.

819
00:30:47,590 --> 00:30:48,850
Then fill in your name,

820
00:30:48,900 --> 00:30:50,110
class, and student ID.

821
00:30:50,110 --> 00:30:51,830
We will organize training later.

822
00:30:51,830 --> 00:30:53,300
I'm not a student here.

823
00:30:53,570 --> 00:30:55,570
Print this out later.

824
00:30:55,700 --> 00:30:56,100
Right.

825
00:30:58,610 --> 00:31:01,210
Our Student Union
isn't open to the outsiders.

826
00:31:01,900 --> 00:31:02,600
Right.

827
00:31:02,750 --> 00:31:03,650
How about this?

828
00:31:03,790 --> 00:31:04,660
You can try the community channel instead.

829
00:31:04,660 --> 00:31:06,000
I'll give you the street office management
contact number.

830
00:31:06,000 --> 00:31:06,590
You can check with them first.

831
00:31:06,590 --> 00:31:07,180
Is that possible?

832
00:31:07,180 --> 00:31:07,630
Yes.

833
00:31:07,810 --> 00:31:09,210
That's great. Thank you.

834
00:31:12,420 --> 00:31:13,490
[Music Conservatory Student Union]

835
00:31:13,510 --> 00:31:14,700
[Summer Work-Study
Program Registration Desk]

836
00:31:27,620 --> 00:31:28,920
Little Northeasterner,

837
00:31:28,920 --> 00:31:30,440
the water isn't hot.

838
00:31:31,740 --> 00:31:33,340
Then wait for the next batch.

839
00:31:33,940 --> 00:31:36,070
It's only 30 degrees. It'll be a while.

840
00:31:37,050 --> 00:31:38,180
The food your dear sister saved for you.

841
00:31:38,180 --> 00:31:38,880
Have you eaten up?

842
00:31:38,880 --> 00:31:40,480
Don't talk nonsense.

843
00:31:43,530 --> 00:31:44,500
This is your first proper meal in days

844
00:31:44,500 --> 00:31:45,560
and it's just this?

845
00:31:46,700 --> 00:31:47,940
Everything tastes bland.

846
00:31:47,940 --> 00:31:48,940
I need something salty.

847
00:31:48,940 --> 00:31:50,740
Didn't you go to the film studio?

848
00:31:52,680 --> 00:31:54,140
Creative work takes time.

849
00:31:54,700 --> 00:31:56,920
I've got to be steady, step by step.
There's time.

850
00:31:56,920 --> 00:31:58,790
Got it. An artist, huh.

851
00:32:01,720 --> 00:32:02,310
Well...

852
00:32:02,590 --> 00:32:05,120
What about next month's rent?
Got it covered?

853
00:32:06,140 --> 00:32:07,190
Honestly,

854
00:32:07,420 --> 00:32:08,770
a lot of people who leave next month

855
00:32:08,770 --> 00:32:10,110
are in the same situation as you—

856
00:32:10,110 --> 00:32:11,110
barely managing,

857
00:32:11,140 --> 00:32:12,290
sometimes only one meal a day,

858
00:32:12,290 --> 00:32:13,550
not even daring to add an egg.

859
00:32:13,550 --> 00:32:14,280
Don't worry.

860
00:32:14,850 --> 00:32:16,380
I'll extend my stay
through the end of the year.

861
00:32:16,380 --> 00:32:16,850
Yes.

862
00:32:17,710 --> 00:32:18,910
I know your industry.

863
00:32:19,640 --> 00:32:20,520
Either nothing for months,

864
00:32:20,520 --> 00:32:21,960
or one job that keeps you
going for half a year.

865
00:32:21,960 --> 00:32:23,330
But who knows

866
00:32:23,480 --> 00:32:25,050
when the next gig will come, right?

867
00:32:25,050 --> 00:32:26,780
I don't do credit here, though.

868
00:32:27,280 --> 00:32:29,050
I've never been in debt in my life.

869
00:32:29,050 --> 00:32:30,510
This is really something.

870
00:32:30,570 --> 00:32:31,180
If I send my scripts

871
00:32:31,180 --> 00:32:32,410
to more film studios,

872
00:32:32,570 --> 00:32:33,970
I can also write articles

873
00:32:34,070 --> 00:32:35,420
and submit them to editorial departments,

874
00:32:35,420 --> 00:32:36,680
magazines, and newspapers.

875
00:32:36,680 --> 00:32:37,940
Those are all ways to make money.

876
00:32:37,940 --> 00:32:38,500
Yes.

877
00:32:39,480 --> 00:32:40,350
I mean

878
00:32:40,660 --> 00:32:42,050
we've got to think
both long-term and short-term,

879
00:32:42,050 --> 00:32:42,640
don't we?

880
00:32:43,150 --> 00:32:44,310
You've got ideals ahead of you,

881
00:32:44,310 --> 00:32:46,310
but in the near term
you still have to eat.

882
00:32:46,310 --> 00:32:48,640
Let's stay and then talk about the future.

883
00:33:02,900 --> 00:33:03,460
Zhuang.

884
00:33:05,400 --> 00:33:06,660
I was just looking for you

885
00:33:06,660 --> 00:33:07,590
and I ran into you here.

886
00:33:07,590 --> 00:33:08,450
Officer Zhang,

887
00:33:09,030 --> 00:33:10,360
you were looking for me?

888
00:33:13,000 --> 00:33:13,540
Look.

889
00:33:13,740 --> 00:33:15,070
Is this the bag you lost?

890
00:33:15,850 --> 00:33:16,800
Yes!

891
00:33:17,380 --> 00:33:19,040
You're an amazing detective.

892
00:33:20,850 --> 00:33:22,450
Did... Did you catch the guy?

893
00:33:22,880 --> 00:33:23,740
Not yet.

894
00:33:24,440 --> 00:33:25,860
A sanitation worker found it.

895
00:33:25,860 --> 00:33:26,920
Your ID was inside,

896
00:33:26,940 --> 00:33:28,270
along with some photos.

897
00:33:28,770 --> 00:33:30,370
The cash is definitely gone.

898
00:33:38,130 --> 00:33:39,680
You're smart, though—

899
00:33:40,220 --> 00:33:41,680
hiding money in a hidden layer.

900
00:33:41,680 --> 00:33:42,680
Here, sign this.

901
00:33:42,850 --> 00:33:43,250
OK.

902
00:33:46,610 --> 00:33:47,940
Thank you, Officer.

903
00:33:48,280 --> 00:33:49,430
You guys are incredible.

904
00:33:49,430 --> 00:33:50,360
You're welcome.

905
00:33:51,030 --> 00:33:51,510
Here.

906
00:33:52,510 --> 00:33:53,220
Thank you.

907
00:33:53,240 --> 00:33:53,880
Sorry for the trouble.

908
00:33:53,880 --> 00:33:54,480
It's fine.

909
00:33:54,660 --> 00:33:56,570
Consider that an unexpected gain.

910
00:33:56,570 --> 00:33:58,140
I'll contact you if there's news.

911
00:33:58,140 --> 00:33:58,780
Thank you.

912
00:33:59,180 --> 00:33:59,790
You're welcome.

913
00:33:59,790 --> 00:34:00,720
I appreciate it.

914
00:34:00,790 --> 00:34:01,390
By the way,

915
00:34:02,360 --> 00:34:04,090
if you have trouble in Beijing,

916
00:34:04,110 --> 00:34:04,810
call the police.

917
00:34:04,810 --> 00:34:05,290
OK!

918
00:34:10,969 --> 00:34:13,260
Will it work without turning on the stove?

919
00:34:13,260 --> 00:34:14,860
This is called a "onsen egg."

920
00:34:15,210 --> 00:34:16,400
You just soak the egg in water

921
00:34:16,400 --> 00:34:17,760
at about 60 to 80 degrees Celsius.

922
00:34:17,760 --> 00:34:18,710
The egg white

923
00:34:18,760 --> 00:34:20,370
sets slightly,

924
00:34:20,610 --> 00:34:22,010
but the yolk stays runny.

925
00:34:22,790 --> 00:34:24,790
It's delicious with some soy sauce.

926
00:34:25,480 --> 00:34:26,780
So that's an onsen egg?

927
00:34:27,710 --> 00:34:28,710
I thought it meant

928
00:34:29,010 --> 00:34:30,460
eating an egg

929
00:34:30,510 --> 00:34:32,170
while soaking in a hot spring.

930
00:34:32,880 --> 00:34:34,880
This egg has a better life than we do.

931
00:34:35,460 --> 00:34:37,659
Things will get better for us soon, too.

932
00:34:38,530 --> 00:34:39,460
Close your eyes.

933
00:34:45,400 --> 00:34:47,000
What are you thinking about?

934
00:35:17,000 --> 00:35:18,500
Where did you

935
00:35:18,500 --> 00:35:19,440
get this money?

936
00:35:23,220 --> 00:35:24,380
You got it back?

937
00:35:27,650 --> 00:35:28,850
The bulk of it is gone.

938
00:35:28,880 --> 00:35:29,550
But fortunately,

939
00:35:29,550 --> 00:35:30,550
I hid a little bit.

940
00:35:32,090 --> 00:35:33,220
You're impressive.

941
00:35:35,940 --> 00:35:36,800
This is for you.

942
00:35:38,380 --> 00:35:39,870
I don't need this much.

943
00:35:40,760 --> 00:35:42,420
Consider the rest a loan.

944
00:35:43,340 --> 00:35:43,960
No need.

945
00:35:44,000 --> 00:35:45,000
I submit articles every day.

946
00:35:45,000 --> 00:35:47,000
I'll get the royalties in a few days.

947
00:35:47,940 --> 00:35:49,530
I'm not that kind-hearted.

948
00:35:50,130 --> 00:35:51,460
I'm charging interest.

949
00:36:05,070 --> 00:36:07,000
This egg isn't having an easy time.

950
00:36:12,400 --> 00:36:14,000
Whether it has a good life or not

951
00:36:14,000 --> 00:36:16,090
depends on whether you
choose a passionate, intense life

952
00:36:16,090 --> 00:36:17,420
or a calm, ordinary one.

953
00:36:18,260 --> 00:36:19,730
That is well said.

954
00:36:20,550 --> 00:36:21,530
Whether it has a good life or not

955
00:36:21,530 --> 00:36:23,030
depends on whether you
choose a passionate, intense life

956
00:36:23,030 --> 00:36:24,360
or a calm, ordinary one.

957
00:36:24,980 --> 00:36:27,110
I gotta write that down when I get back.

958
00:36:27,770 --> 00:36:29,720
A passionate, intense life

959
00:36:31,170 --> 00:36:32,500
or a calm, ordinary one.

960
00:36:43,360 --> 00:36:44,070
I can see

961
00:36:45,230 --> 00:36:46,560
that you really love it.

962
00:36:46,760 --> 00:36:48,020
Just focus on writing.

963
00:36:49,570 --> 00:36:51,370
This money should tide you over.

964
00:36:51,460 --> 00:36:52,800
This weekend,

965
00:36:52,980 --> 00:36:54,380
I'll go check things out.

966
00:36:54,630 --> 00:36:55,960
If I can make some money,

967
00:36:56,840 --> 00:36:58,170
I can lend you a bit more.

968
00:36:59,400 --> 00:37:01,000
You found a way to make money?

969
00:37:02,340 --> 00:37:03,480
You go to class every day,

970
00:37:03,480 --> 00:37:04,840
yet you still have time
to figure this out?

971
00:37:04,840 --> 00:37:06,010
Even if I go to class,
I still need to solve

972
00:37:06,010 --> 00:37:07,340
my immediate problems.

973
00:37:10,320 --> 00:37:10,800
True.

974
00:37:11,000 --> 00:37:12,930
Dreams can't put food on the table.

975
00:37:14,210 --> 00:37:14,610
So,

976
00:37:14,920 --> 00:37:15,650
what exactly is your way

977
00:37:15,650 --> 00:37:16,760
of making money?

978
00:37:17,230 --> 00:37:18,440
I'm keeping it under wraps.

979
00:37:18,440 --> 00:37:19,770
Nothing is certain yet.

980
00:37:20,710 --> 00:37:22,640
Now you're keeping me in suspense.

981
00:37:26,630 --> 00:37:27,170
You two,

982
00:37:27,500 --> 00:37:28,210
what are you doing squatting here—

983
00:37:28,210 --> 00:37:29,170
hatching eggs?

984
00:37:30,340 --> 00:37:31,800
We're hatching golden eggs.

985
00:37:31,800 --> 00:37:32,840
Shiny and gold.

986
00:37:34,420 --> 00:37:36,550
Onsen eggs—golden and shiny.

987
00:37:37,070 --> 00:37:37,600
Alright.

988
00:37:37,960 --> 00:37:39,220
You two keep hatching.

989
00:37:40,920 --> 00:37:42,130
Here, try this.

990
00:37:43,380 --> 00:37:44,180
Look, the yolk

991
00:37:44,420 --> 00:37:45,290
is still runny.

992
00:37:45,690 --> 00:37:46,550
Slurp it first.

993
00:37:46,980 --> 00:37:47,380
Hurry.

994
00:37:47,980 --> 00:37:48,840
Is this cooked?

995
00:37:49,960 --> 00:37:50,420
This...

996
00:37:51,170 --> 00:37:52,370
This is an onsen egg.

997
00:37:52,400 --> 00:37:53,060
It's runny.

998
00:37:53,820 --> 00:37:56,020
Be careful. Don't spill it on yourself.

999
00:37:57,940 --> 00:37:58,470
How is it?

1000
00:37:59,700 --> 00:38:00,800
It's like jelly.

1001
00:38:03,200 --> 00:38:05,000
It's better with some soy sauce.

1002
00:38:10,500 --> 00:38:12,450
Beat the hand drum and sing a song,

1003
00:38:12,480 --> 00:38:15,500
I ride my horse over the mountain slopes.

1004
00:38:17,110 --> 00:38:19,360
On the vast grasslands,
cattle and sheep grow strong,

1005
00:38:19,360 --> 00:38:22,160
and golden waves
shimmer over the harvest fields.

1006
00:38:25,010 --> 00:38:25,670
What are you doing?

1007
00:38:25,670 --> 00:38:26,730
I'm waiting for you.

1008
00:38:26,730 --> 00:38:27,570
Waiting for me?

1009
00:38:27,570 --> 00:38:28,100
For what?

1010
00:38:28,530 --> 00:38:30,990
Didn't you talk about
hatching golden eggs?

1011
00:38:32,750 --> 00:38:34,410
You really took that to heart.

1012
00:38:34,480 --> 00:38:36,540
How can I not care about making money?

1013
00:38:36,570 --> 00:38:38,630
So, how do we hatch these golden eggs?

1014
00:38:38,670 --> 00:38:39,630
It's not decided yet.

1015
00:38:39,630 --> 00:38:40,330
No, no, no.

1016
00:38:40,530 --> 00:38:41,530
Sit down.

1017
00:38:41,690 --> 00:38:42,420
Just sit.

1018
00:38:42,590 --> 00:38:43,920
Stop keeping me in suspense.

1019
00:38:43,920 --> 00:38:45,110
Just tell me.

1020
00:38:46,400 --> 00:38:46,930
Alright.

1021
00:38:49,070 --> 00:38:49,920
I found a spot

1022
00:38:50,170 --> 00:38:51,070
near a school

1023
00:38:51,130 --> 00:38:53,060
where I can set up a clothing stall.

1024
00:38:53,130 --> 00:38:54,380
The daily stall fee

1025
00:38:54,380 --> 00:38:55,440
is only a few dozen yuan.

1026
00:38:55,440 --> 00:38:56,300
I'll use the rest of the money

1027
00:38:56,300 --> 00:38:57,460
to stock up.

1028
00:38:57,570 --> 00:38:58,820
Then if I mark up each item

1029
00:38:58,820 --> 00:38:59,610
by three to five yuan,

1030
00:38:59,610 --> 00:39:00,670
I'll make a profit.

1031
00:39:03,690 --> 00:39:04,690
A stall

1032
00:39:05,010 --> 00:39:05,810
near a school?

1033
00:39:07,230 --> 00:39:09,490
Those spots must be in high demand.

1034
00:39:09,610 --> 00:39:11,190
Besides, with so many stalls,

1035
00:39:11,190 --> 00:39:12,340
can we make any money?

1036
00:39:12,340 --> 00:39:13,670
We have to give it a shot.

1037
00:39:14,630 --> 00:39:15,630
Getting this money back

1038
00:39:15,630 --> 00:39:17,030
was a pleasant surprise.

1039
00:39:17,880 --> 00:39:19,170
I'll use this 400 yuan

1040
00:39:19,260 --> 00:39:20,670
as startup capital.

1041
00:39:22,170 --> 00:39:23,170
I'm confident.

1042
00:39:28,280 --> 00:39:29,340
What are you doing?

1043
00:39:30,880 --> 00:39:31,410
500 yuan.

1044
00:39:31,920 --> 00:39:32,580
Either make

1045
00:39:32,920 --> 00:39:33,530
or break.

1046
00:39:41,190 --> 00:39:41,720
Let's go!

1047
00:39:42,010 --> 00:39:42,540
Let's go.

1048
00:39:44,070 --> 00:39:45,130
Where are we going?

1049
00:39:45,150 --> 00:39:46,080
To buy goods.

1050
00:39:46,360 --> 00:39:47,730
Where are we buying them?

1051
00:39:47,730 --> 00:39:48,130
Guess.

1052
00:39:48,500 --> 00:39:49,100
Me? Guess?

1053
00:39:50,050 --> 00:39:51,460
Then how much are we buying?

1054
00:39:51,460 --> 00:39:52,000
Guess.

1055
00:39:52,500 --> 00:39:53,630
Wait... We are partners;

1056
00:39:53,630 --> 00:39:54,570
why won't you tell me anything?

1057
00:39:54,570 --> 00:39:57,140
[CHUN LAI JIE]

1058
00:39:57,190 --> 00:40:04,300
[Develop Campus Services,
Boost Economic Growth]

1059
00:39:58,670 --> 00:39:59,200
I'm back.

1060
00:40:00,110 --> 00:40:00,510
Boss,

1061
00:40:01,000 --> 00:40:02,320
is it okay to place the rack like this?

1062
00:40:02,320 --> 00:40:02,900
It's fine.

1063
00:40:02,900 --> 00:40:03,900
Hang the clothes.

1064
00:40:05,230 --> 00:40:05,690
Come on.

1065
00:40:06,400 --> 00:40:07,610
I looked at the other stalls

1066
00:40:07,610 --> 00:40:09,300
packed with goods

1067
00:40:09,320 --> 00:40:09,960
and have so many different items.

1068
00:40:09,960 --> 00:40:11,320
Can we really make it
with just this little stock?

1069
00:40:11,320 --> 00:40:13,260
Quality matters more than quantity.

1070
00:40:13,260 --> 00:40:14,260
If I match and style them properly,

1071
00:40:14,260 --> 00:40:15,840
we won't be worse than anyone else.

1072
00:40:15,840 --> 00:40:16,440
Hang it up.

1073
00:40:16,650 --> 00:40:17,210
OK.

1074
00:40:17,380 --> 00:40:18,340
Two-piece outfits go on the left,

1075
00:40:18,340 --> 00:40:19,670
dresses go on the right.

1076
00:40:19,690 --> 00:40:20,090
OK.

1077
00:40:22,760 --> 00:40:23,890
This one goes up too.

1078
00:40:36,170 --> 00:40:36,900
Hang it here?

1079
00:40:39,940 --> 00:40:40,710
Give that to me.

1080
00:40:40,710 --> 00:40:41,440
Give it to me.

1081
00:40:44,130 --> 00:40:45,440
Put this on.

1082
00:40:45,500 --> 00:40:46,230
I put it on?

1083
00:40:46,300 --> 00:40:46,790
Yes.

1084
00:40:46,900 --> 00:40:47,840
We haven't even opened for business yet,

1085
00:40:47,840 --> 00:40:48,820
and you're already giving me a piece?

1086
00:40:48,820 --> 00:40:49,690
In your dreams.

1087
00:40:49,900 --> 00:40:50,430
Put it on.

1088
00:40:51,030 --> 00:40:52,010
I just walked around

1089
00:40:52,010 --> 00:40:53,360
and noticed every stall

1090
00:40:53,380 --> 00:40:54,880
has those mannequin models.

1091
00:40:54,880 --> 00:40:56,280
We're going to do a real-life version—

1092
00:40:56,280 --> 00:40:57,800
more vivid, more eye-catching.

1093
00:40:57,800 --> 00:40:58,760
That works.

1094
00:41:06,070 --> 00:41:07,130
Put it on over here.

1095
00:41:10,050 --> 00:41:11,550
Ma'am, can I use your mirror?

1096
00:41:11,550 --> 00:41:13,010
-Yes, please.
-Thank you.

1097
00:41:13,230 --> 00:41:13,830
Like this?

1098
00:41:15,030 --> 00:41:16,170
Fix the collar properly.

1099
00:41:16,170 --> 00:41:16,610
OK.

1100
00:41:17,400 --> 00:41:18,280
Button it up.

1101
00:41:18,730 --> 00:41:19,460
Button it up.

1102
00:41:19,630 --> 00:41:20,920
Then tuck it into your pants.

1103
00:41:20,920 --> 00:41:21,280
OK.

1104
00:41:23,340 --> 00:41:24,150
How much we can sell

1105
00:41:24,150 --> 00:41:25,030
this shirt for today

1106
00:41:25,030 --> 00:41:26,000
depends on your performance.

1107
00:41:26,000 --> 00:41:27,660
Then... Why don't you wear it?

1108
00:41:27,730 --> 00:41:28,460
Cut the crap.

1109
00:41:28,960 --> 00:41:30,160
Roll up your sleeves.

1110
00:41:30,630 --> 00:41:31,530
Thank you, ma'am.

1111
00:41:31,530 --> 00:41:32,520
It's fine.

1112
00:41:33,190 --> 00:41:34,050
You look sharp.

1113
00:41:34,650 --> 00:41:35,230
Thank you.

1114
00:41:35,230 --> 00:41:35,830
It's fine.

1115
00:41:39,180 --> 00:41:39,810
Boss,

1116
00:41:40,440 --> 00:41:41,930
since we're new here,

1117
00:41:42,000 --> 00:41:42,670
should I go

1118
00:41:42,710 --> 00:41:43,550
to the nearby vendors

1119
00:41:43,550 --> 00:41:44,350
and say hello?

1120
00:41:44,460 --> 00:41:46,000
That way we can look out for each other.

1121
00:41:46,000 --> 00:41:47,460
Why didn't I think of that?

1122
00:41:48,760 --> 00:41:49,590
Then buy some water

1123
00:41:49,590 --> 00:41:50,480
and bring it to them.

1124
00:41:50,480 --> 00:41:51,400
Just deduct it from the petty cash.

1125
00:41:51,400 --> 00:41:51,860
No need.

1126
00:41:52,420 --> 00:41:54,020
I'll use my own little stash.

1127
00:41:56,920 --> 00:41:57,710
Come back again!

1128
00:41:57,710 --> 00:41:58,420
OK. Thank you, sis.

1129
00:41:58,420 --> 00:41:59,460
I'll save a nice one for you.

1130
00:41:59,460 --> 00:41:59,900
OK.

1131
00:42:01,150 --> 00:42:02,760
This won't do.

1132
00:42:02,820 --> 00:42:04,620
You have to move the stall aside.

1133
00:42:04,710 --> 00:42:05,670
Or you'll block the path.

1134
00:42:05,670 --> 00:42:06,840
You can't lack public spirit.

1135
00:42:06,840 --> 00:42:07,790
Right?

1136
00:42:08,110 --> 00:42:08,950
Your two shops

1137
00:42:08,980 --> 00:42:09,820
are too close together.

1138
00:42:09,820 --> 00:42:11,260
Don't block other people's business.

1139
00:42:11,260 --> 00:42:11,480
OK.

1140
00:42:11,480 --> 00:42:12,680
That won't do either.

1141
00:42:12,900 --> 00:42:13,920
Don't litter.

1142
00:42:13,960 --> 00:42:14,670
Don't throw trash around.

1143
00:42:14,670 --> 00:42:15,470
Do you hear me?

1144
00:42:16,980 --> 00:42:17,840
I think you guys

1145
00:42:17,880 --> 00:42:19,540
-sell this in summer...
-Sis.

1146
00:42:19,860 --> 00:42:20,460
Young man,

1147
00:42:21,650 --> 00:42:22,500
you mentioned

1148
00:42:22,980 --> 00:42:24,170
that Wenzhou girl just now…

1149
00:42:24,170 --> 00:42:24,760
Hello.

1150
00:42:26,280 --> 00:42:28,760
This girl is really pretty.

1151
00:42:28,840 --> 00:42:30,130
Are you from Wenzhou too?

1152
00:42:30,130 --> 00:42:30,780
Yes.

1153
00:42:31,690 --> 00:42:32,820
So nice. So pretty.

1154
00:42:33,050 --> 00:42:33,820
Thank you.

1155
00:42:34,040 --> 00:42:40,040
[Trendy Clothing Shop]

1156
00:42:34,140 --> 00:42:34,630
Look.

1157
00:42:34,820 --> 00:42:36,020
My shop is right here.

1158
00:42:36,940 --> 00:42:37,630
My child

1159
